c and the Wesleys|date=2010|publisher=University of Illinois Press|isbn=9780252077678|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vAI1EZNzJAkC&pg=PA145&lpg=PA145&dq=Nelme+Rogers+St+Mary+Redcliffe#v=onepage&q=Nelme%20Rogers%20St%20Mary%20Redcliffe&f=false|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Traill|first1=Henry Duff|title=Coleridge|date=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9781108034449|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DPO583uhPhAC&pg=PA20&lpg=PA20&dq=st+mary+redcliffe+Coleridge#v=onepage&q=st%20mary%20redcliffe%20Coleridge&f=false|ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|St Mary Redcliffe}}\n*[http://www.stmaryredcliffe.co.uk/ Official site]\n*[http://www.medart.pitt.edu/image/England/Bristol/StMaryRedcliffe/Bristol-StMarysRed.html St Mary's Redcliffe Parish Church&nbsp;\u2013 dimensions and plans]\n\n{{Greater Churches}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint Mary Redcliffe}}\n[[Category:Churches completed in 1872]]\n[[Category:12th-century churches in the United Kingdom|Redcliffe]]\n[[Category:15th-century church buildings in England|Redcliffe]]\n[[Category:Church of England church buildings in Bristol|Redcliffe]]\n[[Category:Diocese of Bristol|Redcliffe]]\n[[Category:Grade I listed churches in Bristol|Redcliffe, St Mary]]\n[[Category:Music venues in Bristol]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Bristol]]\n", "name_user": "Nickuae", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMonuments and memorials", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St_Mary_Redcliffe"}
